## 1. Overview

This system is a **multi-agent AI assistant** built on the **OpenClaw** runtime. A user
talks to it in natural language over **WhatsApp** (and later email); OpenClaw interprets the
request, routes it to the right specialized agent/skill, queries the MLS databases, and
returns a formatted answer — all in real time.

The two data sources are MySQL tables in the same schema:

- **`rets_property`** — active California listings, 130+ fields (live search & discovery).
- **`california_sold`** — sold/closed transactions, 46 fields (market analytics & comps).

---

## 2. OpenClaw Core Concepts

OpenClaw is a multi-agent orchestration runtime that handles skill routing, session state,
channel integration, and tool execution. The building blocks:

| Component | Role |
|-----------|------|
| **Channels** | Communication interfaces — WhatsApp, email, web. Entry/exit point for messages. |
| **Orchestrator** | Classifies each query's intent and routes it to the correct skill/agent (or several). |
| **Skills** | Modular capability units — property search, market stats, recommendations, RAG, email. |
| **Tools** | Typed async functions a skill can call (e.g., a parameterized SQL query). |
| **Sessions** | Per-user conversation state and short-term memory (budget, city, last results, step). |
| **Memory** | Short-term session state + long-term vector storage (embeddings for semantic search). |

