## 3. End-to-End Request Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    U([User]) -->|natural language| WA[WhatsApp Channel]
    WA --> RT[OpenClaw Runtime]
    RT --> SES[(Session / Memory)]
    RT --> ORCH{Orchestrator<br/>intent classification}

    ORCH -->|search| PS[Property Search Agent]
    ORCH -->|market| MS[Market Stats Agent]
    ORCH -->|recommend| RE[Recommendation Agent]
    ORCH -->|knowledge| RAG[RAG Knowledge Agent]
    ORCH -->|email| EM[Email Draft Agent]

    PS --> DB1[(rets_property<br/>active listings)]
    RE --> DB1
    MS --> DB2[(california_sold<br/>sold comps)]
    RE --> DB2
    RAG --> KB[(Indexed docs +<br/>MLS field definitions)]

    PS --> FMT[Format Response]
    MS --> FMT
    RE --> FMT
    RAG --> FMT
    EM -->|draft, needs approval| FMT

    FMT --> WA
    WA -->|formatted reply| U
```

**Step by step:**

1. **User → WhatsApp Channel** — the user sends a free-text message (e.g., *"3-bed condos in Irvine under $1.5M with a pool"*).
2. **Channel → Runtime** — OpenClaw receives the message and loads the user's **session**.
3. **Orchestrator** — classifies intent: `search`, `market`, `recommend`, `knowledge`, or `mixed`.
4. **Skill/Agent execution** — the chosen agent runs its **tools** (parameterized SQL against `rets_property` / `california_sold`, embedding similarity, or RAG retrieval).
5. **Memory update** — results and preferences are written back to the session for follow-ups.
6. **Format response** — output is formatted into clean WhatsApp message cards.
7. **Reply → User** — the answer is sent back over the same channel.

