## 4. Specialized Agents (built over Weeks 2–8, unified in Week 9)

| Agent | Primary table(s) | Responsibility |
|-------|------------------|----------------|
| Property Search | `rets_property` | NL query → structured filters → listing results |
| Market Stats | `california_sold` | Aggregations: avg/median price, DOM, list-to-close, trends |
| Recommendation | both | Hybrid (structured + semantic) similarity, comp-validated pricing |
| RAG Knowledge | indexed docs | Grounded answers about MLS fields & real-estate terms |
| Email Draft | both | Drafts alerts/reports — **send only after human approval** |

---

## 5. Data Layer

- Both tables live in one MySQL schema (`idx_exchange`); joined via
  `rets_property.L_ListingID = california_sold.ListingKey`, or matched on city + postal
  code for market-level analysis.
- All queries are **parameterized** (no string concatenation) for SQL-injection safety.
- Result sets are capped (≤50 rows/query); raw datasets are never bulk-exported.

---

## 6. Safety / Guardrails (applied from Week 11)

- **Human-in-the-loop** for every outbound action (emails are drafted, never auto-sent).
- Secrets (`OPENAI_API_KEY`, DB credentials) live only in `.env`, never committed or logged.
- The agent never exposes credentials or bulk-downloads full MLS data.

